cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper focuses on visual keyword spotting for words unseen during training, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes the use of a grapheme-to-phoneme model based on sequence-to-sequence neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
